t from `role`, `content_text`, `tool_name`,\n    33\t   `event_kind`, and redacted `source_record`\n    34\t\n    35\tThat means the transcript list must be readable without knowing the original\n    36\tmachine's file paths, working-directory state, branch state, or raw provider\n    37\tsession id.\n    38\t\n    39\t## 2. Sharing Session Details\n    40\t\n    41\tA developer uses an agent to produce a change and opens a pull re\n[TRUNCATED]\n's transcript timeline from the slim envelope fields\n    66\t5. use redacted `source_record` for provenance and later normalization upgrades\n    67\t\n    68\tThat means branch/PR metadata should point to sessions, not contain copies of\n    69\tsession transcripts.\n    70\t\n    71\t## Many-to-Many Relationships\n    72\t\n    73\tSessions and code review objects are not one-to-one.\n    74\t\n    75\tOne branch or pull request may involve multiple sessions:\n    76\t\n    77\t```text\n    78\tPR A\n    79\t  -> session 1\n    80\t  -> session 2\n    81\t```\n    82\t\n    83\tOne session may also contribute to multiple branches or pull requests, especially\n    84\tin GitButler where a worktree can contain several active branches and a user may\n    85\tcommit different hunks to different destinations:\n    86\t\n    87\t```text\n    88\tsession 1\n    89\t  -> feature branch\n    90\t  -> bugfix branch\n    91\t```\n    92\t\n    93\tThe durable object should therefore be the project-scoped GitButler agent\n    94\tsession. Branches, commits, changes, and pull requests should later reference\n    95\tsession keys rather than own the transcript data directly.\n    96\t\n    97\tThis is especially important for GitButler because a single worktree may contain\n    98\tmultiple active branches at once. An agent can produce edits that the user later\n    99\tsplits across several branches, so the capture layer should not guess ownership\n   100\tfrom the current branch.\n   101\t\n   102\tFuture relationship keys can look like this:\n   103\t\n   104\t```text\n   105\t<branch/change/commit target>\n   106\t  gitbutler:agent-sessions = set<session-key>\n   107\t```\n   108\t\n   109\tThat shape supports:\n   110\t\n   111\t- sessions that exist before code is written\n   112\t- one session associated with many branch or review objects\n   113\t- many sessions associated with one branch or review object\n   114\t- branch or commit associations being added after capture\n   115\t\n   116\t## POC Direction\n   117\t\n   118\tThe first POC should:\n   119\t\n   120\t- write redacted, shareable-ready `gitbutler:*` keys\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-09T18:31:24.350Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}